13/09/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Progress in implementing required reforms and co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal are the key conditions for relaxing the EU visa regime for BiH, High Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling said on Tuesday (12 September). Speaking during an NGO-organised roundtable on visa issues in Sarajevo, he said working towards a visa-free future is a top priority for him. He added that other pending matters include the restructuring of the police sector, adoption of measures regulating the issuance of residence permits, preparations for the introduction of new biometric passports, and strengthening border security control. (OHR Sources, RTRS - 12/09/06)
